\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Weekly Multi-Board Job Search with Resume Scoring\
\
**Purpose:** Weekly comprehensive search across major job boards with AI-powered resume matching  \
**Frequency:** Run every Sunday  \
**Runtime:** ~8-12 minutes (depending on result volume)  \
**Prerequisites:** Resume attachment required\
\
---\
\
## Prompt Template\
\
Search these job boards for roles posted in the last 7 days:\
- site:ashbyhq.com\
- site:jobs.lever.co\
- site:boards.greenhouse.io\
\
**Roles:**\
- Chief of Staff\
- Partnerships\
- [ADD THIRD ROLE AS NEEDED]\
\
**Locations:**\
- [CITY 1, COUNTRY]\
- [CITY 2, COUNTRY]\
\
Show progress matrix as you search each board/role/location combination.\
\
**Extract fields** (use "N/A" if not available):\
- Company\
- Company Sector\
- Job Title\
- Location\
- Salary (convert to USD if listed in other currency)\
- Work Arrangement (Remote/Hybrid/In-Office)\
- Job Summary (1-2 sentences)\
- URL\
\
**Deduplication:** Eliminate duplicate jobs (same company + same job title across boards). Keep highest-scoring version and list all boards where found in "Found_On" column.\
\
**Scoring:** Using attached resume (Joey_Clark_Resume_2026.pdf), score each job 1-100:\
- Skills fit (40 points)\
- Industry alignment (35 points)\
- Experience match (25 points)\
\
Provide 1-2 sentence score rationale for each job.\
\
Filter to jobs scoring 70+ only. Rank by score (highest to lowest).\
\
**New Job Detection:** Compare against /Users/jc3/JobSearch/results/Week_of_[LAST_WEEK_DATE]/Week_[LAST_WEEK_DATE]_MasterList.csv\
\
- If file exists: Mark jobs not in previous file as "NEW"\
- If file doesn't exist (first run): Mark all jobs as "NEW"\
- Add "Status" column with "NEW" or "Repeat"\
\
**Output Files:**\
\
1. **Master List:** /Users/jc3/JobSearch/results/Week_of_[YYYY-MM-DD]/Master_List_[YYYY-MM-DD].csv\
   \
   Columns: Status | Score | Score_Rationale | Company | Job_Title | Sector | Location | Work_Arrangement | Salary_USD | Job_Summary | URL | Found_On\
\
2. **Top 10 New:** /Users/jc3/JobSearch/results/Week_of_[YYYY-MM-DD]/Current_Top10_[YYYY-MM-DD].csv\
   \
   Same columns, only top 10 jobs marked "NEW". If <10 new jobs, include all new jobs. If zero new jobs, create file with headers and note "No new jobs this week."\
\
3. **Save Prompt:** /Users/jc3/JobSearch/searches/prompts/Weekly_Search_[YYYY-MM-DD].txt\
\
Verify all files saved. Show final summary table of top results.\
\
